text: Hansje Bunschoten (3 May 1958 – 1 October 2017) was a freestyle swimmer and television presenter from the Netherlands. She competed for her native country at the 1972 Summer Olympics in Munich, West Germany. As a member of the Dutch Relay Teams she finished in fifth place, both in the 4 × 100 m medley and the 4 × 100 m freestyle.Hansje Bunschoten . sports-reference.com. ncrvgids.nl (interview in Dutch) Bunschoten was born in Hilversum and died of complications from breast cancer in Berlin on 1 October 2017 at the age of 59. ==References== ==Other websites== Category:1958 births Category:2017 deaths Category:1972 Summer Olympics Category:Cancer deaths in Germany Category:Deaths from breast cancer Category:Dutch journalists Category:Olympians for the Netherlands Category:Dutch swimmers Category:Dutch television presenters Category:Sportspeople from Hilversum Category:Sports commentators Category:Sportswomen
